@node REQ "Requirements"

The system requirements have gone up by some amount since the first release of PealIt!Pro - no more 1MB Floppy systems now...

Minimum Requirements:
	Amiga OS 3.0 or greater,
	'020 CPU or better,
	2MB RAM,
	Hard disk,
	MUI and AHI must be installed.

If you are using the standard Amiga sound hardware, CPU mixing is used, which may be rather limited on a basic '020 system, so a faster CPU is advisable. On my 50MHz '030, you can achieve the necessary 8 channels (in 14 bit) with reasonable quality.

Sound cards should also be supported thanks to AHI, although I cannot test this myself.

@endnode

@node REGIST "Registration"

Please note that PealIt!Pro is shareware, and requires a keyfile from me in order for all the features to be enabled. Until you register, the following take effect:
	- You can only use 5 bells - The registered version lets you use 3 to 8 bells.
	- You can only Load in the supplied Place Notation Library, and you cannot Save.
	- The supplied Place Notation Library is limited to 20 entries.
	- You cannot call Bob or Single Lead Heads (both using predefined sequences or calling when playing).
	- You cannot change the Playback Settings

Hopefully this is not too restricting - you can still create methods to play back, mess around with the supplied place notations, and you can still practise playing a bell yourself. Hopefully you will like the program and register to get all the features...

When you register, I will send you a keyfile which you should copy into the same drawer as the PealItPro program (will be explained in an accompanying readme) to enable all the features. I will also send you a Place Notation Library contating over 80 5 bell methods (and any others that I may have).

Note that keyfiles are personalised, so pirates beware!

Registration costs 10UK Pounds (or alternatively, I will accept 20 US Dollars). Send money in cash or cheque to the following address, depending on the time of year:

